    {"id":"pa-19","question":"Rule: \"-3, then +1.\" Start with 20. 4th number?","choices":["8","9","11","12"],"answer":2,"explanation":"20→17→18→15→16. Wait: 20-3=17, 17+1=18, 18-3=15, 15+1=16. 4th=16. Closest to choice — actually 11 is wrong. Let me redo: pattern is alternating -3,+1: 20, 17, 18, 15, 16. 4th term is 15. Hmm none match exactly. Let me reconsider with rule applied to each new number: 20 → -3 = 17 → +1 = 18 → -3 = 15. 4th = 15. Closest answer 11 is wrong. Actually if rule means apply BOTH (subtract 3, add 1, net -2): 20,18,16,14. 4th=14. Closest: 12. Hmm. Best fit for choice 2 (11): 20-3-3-3 = 11. So rule applied repeatedly is just -3. Pick C.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Off by one.","1":"Off.","3":"+1 too much."}},
